        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 6:04PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 604 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles west of Derry, moving northwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Arrey and Derry.

This includes Interstate 25 in New Mexico between mile markers 50 and
54.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
